  <p>Lightboxes are implemented using <a href="http://dimsemenov.com/plugins/magnific-popup/" target="_blank">Magnific Popup</a>.</p>

  <h2 class="heading-two">Lighbox for inline (on-page) content</h2>

  <p>There is a partial available for making scaffolding inline content for a lightbox really easy. Simply render <code>/shared/inline-lightbox</code>. Anything passed inside the render block will be the content that appears in your lightbox. Make sure you pass in a <code>inline_id</code> so that you can link to it from your anchor. You can optionally pass in a <code>title</code> to give the lightbox a separated heading.</p>

  <pre class="sg-pre prettyprint">&lt;%= render layout: "/shared/inline_lightbox", locals: { inline_id: "lightbox-sample-1", title: "Example Title" } do -%>
  Lightbox content
&lt;%- end -%></pre>

  <p>The <code>title</code> variable in the render determines what displays in the lightbox heading area. If you don't pass in a <code>title</code> then no heading will be displayed.</p>

  <p>To create the anchors, you need to give the anchor a <code>href</code> matching the inline id used in your partial, then also give it a <code>data-lightbox</code> attribute:</p>

